                                      InputStream inputData,
                                      boolean isBatch)
                                        throws ExperimentCreationException,
                                               ExperimentDuplicationException,
                                               ExperimentConcurrentAccessException,
                                               ExperimentDataManipulationException
        Description copied from interface: ExperimentCRUDService
        Creates a new experiment case with the given information Updates the given experiment so that it contains the newly created experiment case
        Specified by:
        createExperimentCase in interface ExperimentCRUDService
        Parameters:
        experiment - the experiment the newly created case will belong to
        name - the String name of the experiment case
        ownerName - the String name of the owner of the case
        inputData - an InputStream with input data for the case
        isBatch - true if the input data contains data for multiple cases, false if it contains data for a single case
        Returns:
        the experiment case created
        Throws:
        ExperimentCreationException - if the case cannot be created for other reasons, such as an unacceptable case name or an I/O problem
        ExperimentDuplicationException - if a case by the given name already exists for the provided experiment
        ExperimentConcurrentAccessException - if the given experiment contained old data which was modified concurrently before calling this method to add cases
        ExperimentDataManipulationException - if there is a problem accessing storage which the invoker is expected to act upon
        See Also:

        description - the String description of the experiment, to be used in a loose comparison, null or empty if this criteria should not be applied
